sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant UI as React UI
    participant Store as Zustand
    participant API as FastAPI
    participant GPT4o as GPT-4o
    participant GT as Google Trends
    participant Mini as GPT-4o-mini
    participant ML as HGBR Models
    participant VS as Visual Service

    rect rgb(210,235,255)
        Note over User,Store: ① Profile — collect bio + follower count
        User->>UI: Enter bio + followers → "Analyze Trends"
        UI->>API: POST /api/trends {profile_text, followers}
        API->>GPT4o: Extract 8–12 topics from bio
        GPT4o-->>API: [topic list]
        loop For each uncached topic
            API->>GT: Fetch trend score + queries
            GT-->>API: trend_score, top_queries, rising_queries
        end
        API-->>UI: TrendingTopic[]
        UI->>Store: setTrendingTopics() · setStep(2)
    end

    rect rgb(210,255,220)
        Note over User,Store: ② Topics — pick a focus topic (or let AI choose)
        User->>UI: Select topic card (optional) → "Generate Titles"
        UI->>API: POST /api/post-titles {topics, profile_text, chosen_topic}
        API->>GPT4o: Analyze rising/breakout signals → 3 post titles
        GPT4o-->>API: SIGNAL N: … POST TITLE N: …
        API-->>UI: PostTitle[] (parsed by regex)
        UI->>Store: setPostTitles() · setStep(3)
    end

    rect rgb(255,245,210)
        Note over User,Store: ③ Post Title — choose 1 of 3 titles
        User->>UI: Select title card → "Generate Posts"
        UI->>API: POST /api/post-variants {post_title, profile_text}
        par Contrarian hook
            API->>Mini: Generate post variant
            Mini-->>API: ~150-word post
        and Personal Transformation hook
            API->>Mini: Generate post variant
            Mini-->>API: ~150-word post
        and Hidden Insight hook
            API->>Mini: Generate post variant
            Mini-->>API: ~150-word post
        end
        API-->>UI: PostVariant[3]
        UI->>Store: setPostVariants() · setStep(4)
    end

    rect rgb(255,225,225)
        Note over User,Store: ④ Posts — predict engagement, pick best variant
        UI->>UI: useEffect on mount
        par Predict variant 1
            UI->>API: POST /api/predict {post_text, followers, post_title}
            API->>ML: extract_features() → HGBR.predict() → expm1()
            ML-->>API: {reactions, comments}
            API-->>UI: EngagementPrediction
        and Predict variant 2
            UI->>API: POST /api/predict
            ML-->>API: {reactions, comments}
            API-->>UI: EngagementPrediction
        and Predict variant 3
            UI->>API: POST /api/predict
            ML-->>API: {reactions, comments}
            API-->>UI: EngagementPrediction
        end
        UI->>Store: setPredictions() — mark "best" by reactions+comments
        User->>UI: Click "Select This Post"
        UI->>Store: setFinalPost() · setStep(5)
    end

    rect rgb(235,215,255)
        Note over User,Store: ⑤ Final — copy post + auto-generate visual
        UI->>UI: useEffect on mount → fetchVisual()
        UI->>API: POST /api/visual {post_text}
        API->>VS: subprocess: visual_service.py post_text
        VS->>VS: classify_llm() → "diagram" or "image"
        alt Diagram
            VS->>VS: render_graphviz(dot_code) → PNG
        else Image
            VS->>VS: generate_image(prompt) → PNG
        end
        VS-->>API: stdout JSON {type, path}
        API->>API: base64_encode(PNG) · delete file
        API-->>UI: {image_data: base64, content_type}
        UI->>UI: Display post + inline image
        opt Custom prompt entered
            User->>UI: Type prompt → "Regenerate"
            UI->>API: POST /api/visual {post + custom_prompt}
            API-->>UI: New image
        end
        User->>UI: "Copy to Clipboard"
    end
